rent flow supporting the\nstructured (\"striped\") upstream magnetic field induces a transition to\nsuperluminal wave propagation. I show that current starvation probably does not\noccur, because those currents are carried in the current sheet separating there\nstripes rather than in the stripes themselves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Aug 2012 20:43:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-08-30"}
